[3] Texas (El Paso)
Date: Wed 17 Jul 2019
Source: KTSM [edited]
https://www.ktsm.com/local/el-paso-news/toddler-diagnosed-as-the-fourth-case-of-measles-in-el-paso/


A 3rd toddler has been diagnosed with measles, marking El Paso's 4th confirmed case of the virus. The City of El Paso Department of Public Health confirmed a toddler boy had tested positive for measles in a news release on Wed [17 Jul 2019]. This is the 4th case in 2 weeks after 25 years without one case in El Paso.

"We need our community to focus on making sure that they are up-to-date with their measles or MMR vaccine," said Robert Resendes, public health director in a release. "When we vaccinate ourselves and our children we are not only protecting ourselves and our family, but also reducing the chances of the disease spreading to others in our community."

According to the release, the virus is "very contagious" and 90% of people not vaccinated will be infected if they are exposed to someone with measles.

[byline: Aaron Bracamontes]

--
communicated by:
