<promed@promedmail.org>

[Also see announcement of the 3rd case: (https://www.ktsm.com/life-health-2/health-and-medical/toddler-becomes-third-el-pasoan-to-test-positive-for-measles-in-one-week/). "The announcement [of the 3rd case] comes just days after a woman and another toddler also tested positive for the virus -- the city's first 2 cases in more than 25 years.

"'Because El Paso's immunization rates are so high, we don't expect to see a huge number of cases emerge,' public health director Robert Resendes said. 'We know that the effectiveness of the vaccine, especially after the recommended 2 doses, is about 97%.'

"Health officials say the 2nd toddler is not believed to have exposed the public to the measles, but anyone experiencing said ailments is encouraged to visit a doctor." - Mod.LK

