Auckland Regional Public Health Service (ARPHS) is alerting passengers on weekend flights between Auckland and Palmerston North that they may have been exposed to measles [see source URL above for locations of possible exposure]. So far in 2019, 227 confirmed cases of measles have been reported in Auckland.

